  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4083116268" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4083116268" />
    <a title="Vince" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/128225739-vince"><img alt="Vince" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629724401p2/128225739.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4083116268?book_show_action=true">Jul 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vince" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vince" href="/user/show/128225739-vince">Vince</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4083116268" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16311683861689774800"><b>Every man is said to have his peculiar ambition. Whether it be true or not, I can say for one that I have no other ambition so great as that of being truly esteemed of my fellow men, by rendering myself worthy of their esteem. How far I shall succeed in gratifying this ambition, is yet to be developed.</b> --- <i> Lincoln</i><br/><br/>I think we can all safely say that Lincoln amply succeeded. Well this tome took me a while to finish. About four months. Not only for its size but I&apos;m not a history buff so I read it i</span>
  <span id="freeText16311683861689774800" style="display:none"><b>Every man is said to have his peculiar ambition. Whether it be true or not, I can say for one that I have no other ambition so great as that of being truly esteemed of my fellow men, by rendering myself worthy of their esteem. How far I shall succeed in gratifying this ambition, is yet to be developed.</b> --- <i> Lincoln</i><br /><br />I think we can all safely say that Lincoln amply succeeded. Well this tome took me a while to finish. About four months. Not only for its size but I'm not a history buff so I read it in short bursts because I would get bored if I read too much at one time. I would take it 20 pages a day and the book is 916 pages. Though a great deal of those pages are notes and errata. To be technically correct it took my nearly 38 days to complete and I usually fly through books. Anyway, enough about me let's talk Team of Rivals. This book works as a biography of not only Lincoln but his rivals as well. Everybody from William H.Seward, Lincoln's Secretary of State; Salmon P. Chase, Secretary of the Treasury; and Edwin Stanton, Secretary of Defense and many more. Lincoln's political genius kept these men in check during the brutal and tumultuous years of the Civil War. I won't say how but let you read it for yourself. But know that this book will be vastly informative, beautifully written and by the end emotionally moving. Spoiler Alert: Lincoln gets assassinated and the way the author describes it moved me to tears and I hardly cry from books anymore. Even if you're not a historian, I strongly urge you to give this large book a try. 4 out of 5.<br /><br /><b> I never, in my life, have I felt more certain that I was doing right, than I do in signing this paper. If my name ever goes into history it will be for this act, and my whole soul is in it</b>---- <br /><br /><i> Lincoln signing the Emancipation Proclamation</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="16311683861689774800" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


